playerCharacter.name: khb
playerCharacter.backstory:
Khb was forged in the relentless gears of the Iron Cohort. For a decade, he was a nameless instrument of the state, marching under banners that shifted with the seasons. He fought not for glory or gods, but because the whistle blew and the line had to hold. He saw heroes fall in the mud and villains rewarded with gold, eventually realizing that morality is a luxury the dying cannot afford.

When his legion was finally sacrificed for a strategic withdrawal, Khb walked away from the carnagenot with spite, but with clarity. He kept his scarred gambeson and a heavy, notched blade, transitioning from a soldier of the realm to a soldier of himself. He now occupies the gray space between kingdoms, indifferent to the grand designs of lords. Khb does not seek to save the world or to burn it; he simply survives by the cold, functional grace of his steel.
